abstract: Jon Caramanica reviews albums released by hip-hop group Juggaknots, R&B singer Kehlani and hip-hop dance performer Nick Catchdubs, along with country music compilation album Orthophonic Joy: The 1927 Bristol Sessions Revisited, released by Birthplace of Country Music Museum.
lead_paragraph: New releases also include “Baby Pictures,” a compilation of early tracks by Juggaknots, and “Orthophonic Joy,” a compilation of covers of country music classics.

headline.main: Kehlani and Nick Catchdubs Release New Albums
headline.print_headline: Fresh R&B, Retro Hip-Hop, Foundational Country
